{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ANFiW9nNXQPjnQv7B9ejHD","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `rate-api` ingress already has rate limiting annotations:\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier: \"1\"`\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: \"1\"`\n- `nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-status-code: \"429\"`\n\nHowever, the task says \"/api is not currently rate limited.\" Let me check what's happening - maybe with 3 replicas needed but only 1 running, or maybe the rate limiting annotations are there but not working properly because the annotations were added separately (it shows the `last-applied-configuration` doesn't have the annotations, suggesting they were added later).\nI'm noticing the ingress-nginx controller only has 1 running pod when the task mentions 3 replicas. The real issue is that with multiple replicas, each one maintains its own rate limit counter, so the effective limit becomes 3x the configured value. To enforce a true 1 rps across all replicas, I'd need to either adjust the limit per replica or use a different rate limiting approach.\n\nLooking at the actual ingress configuration, the rate limiting annotations are already there on the `rate-api` ingress, but the task says it's not currently rate limited. This suggests the annotations might not be taking effect—possibly because they were added after the original manifest was applied, or the controller hasn't reloaded the configuration yet.\n\nThe deployment is supposed to have 3 replicas, but I'm only seeing 1 pod running. Let me test whether the rate limiting is actually working in its current state.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":913,"cache_read_input_tokens":31190,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":913},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inferen