{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_018ycFK78iB4a321VX5kqLUz","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture. The precondition is supposed to scale the controller to 3 replicas. The fact that it's at 1 replica means the precondition might have been applied partially, or it was inherited from another stage.\n\nThe oracle is `python3 cases/nginx-ingress/rate_limit_replica_hard/oracle/oracle.py`. Let me read that oracle to understand what it checks.\n\nAlso importantly: the task says \"/api is not currently rate limited\" - but I can see from my test that 429 responses ARE appearing. This could be because the rate-api ingress already has the annotations from a previous stage configuration.\n \nThe real challenge here is that with 3 replicas, simple per-ingress annotations won't work since each replica maintains its own counter. I need to find a way to enforce rate limiting across all replicas—either through a shared ConfigMap with `limit-req-zone` configuration, or by using nginx snippets with lua-based rate limiting that can coordinate across instances.\n\nThe most practical approach would be using `global-rate-limit` annotations backed by memcached or redis to maintain shared state across the replicas. Let me check what the test actually validates to see which approach is expected.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2738,"cache_read_input_tokens":39637,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2738},"output_tokens":27,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"a8cd1c1a-a01d-41e8-9132-726291ea0e35","uuid":"7358f2b3-de1b-44f7-878d-03b48b5510a4","request_id":"req_011CcLwid2ttXDzj34SnL8D8"}
